  <description>
    <p>
      Servo is an experimental web browser engine designed for applications including embedded use.
      Written in Rust, it's being developed on 64-bit macOS, 64-bit Linux, 64-bit Windows, and Android.
    </p>
    <p>
      Servo is built on top of Rust to provide a secure and reliable foundation. It leverages the
      memory safety guarantees of Rust to help avoid common browser vulnerabilities. The project aims
      to create a highly parallel browser engine that takes advantage of modern multi-core processors.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is a testing build packaged as Flatpak for easy installation and distribution. It fetches
      the latest Servo release automatically and packages it for Linux systems.
    </p>
    <p>
      Note: Servo is experimental software and may not work with all websites. It is primarily
      intended for developers and testers who want to explore the future of browser engine technology.
    </p>
  </description>
